{
  "doc_id": "54180",
  "text": "Among SNXs, SNX27 is unique in that it has a PDZ (postsynaptic density protein-95, Discs-large, Zona-occludens-1) domain, which functions as a scaffold to organize various proteins. Efficient recycling of b 2 -AR is dependent on its C-terminal PDZ-domain binding motif [CITATION_1] . Recently, SNX27 has been reported to be a prerequisite for efficient PDZ-directed recycling of various receptors such as b 2 -AR, N-methyl-D-aspartate receptor 2C or glutamate receptors from EE to PM [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . SNX27 might be involved in the functional regulation of many proteins with PDZ-domain binding motifs [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] ). Furthermore, it was shown that SNX27 mediates the recycling of PDZ-domain binding motif-containing cargo, b 2 -AR, by linking to the retromer, a complex of proteins that has been shown to be important in recycling [CITATION_7] . A large number of proteins were shown to be recycled by an SNX27/retromer complex [CITATION_8] ).",
